= A guide to FFII mailing lists  =

== If you have little time (for example, if you are a journalist)  ==

 * subscribe [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/news news] (English) or [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/neues neues] (German) or [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/fr-news actualit√©s] (French).

== If you want to learn about software patents and discuss theoretical issues  ==

 * subscribe [http://www.aful.org/wws/subrequest/patents patents] (English) or [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/swpat swpat] (German) 

== If you do not want to have software patents and want to help FFII  ==

=== Which lists shall I subscribe ?  ===

There is also a [http://news.ffii.org/ news interface to most of these lists]. Some of the lists have [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo public archives].

A meaningful combination could be to subscribe one or two [http://www.ffii.org/~arebenti/ekarte regional lists] (country, and, if existing, region or city), one or two [http://www.ffii.org/proj/list/index.en.html project] lists (see below). If your list(s) are too silent and you like to be on a high-volume catch-all list, the [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/bxl bxl list] is of interest, it discusses "Brussels-related events", de facto anything that happens at the European Institutions in Brussels, Strasbourg or Luxembourg.

=== General structure of lists (what is news, parl, help) ===

In this case, please take a little more time. Registration to mailing lists can be done by http://aktiv.ffii.org/, please register there. 
Most mailing lists are grouped around projects. Let's talk about the project 'europarl' (European Parliament). As most other projects, it has three lists: europarl-news, europarl-parl, and europarl-help. The '-help' stands for 'Helpdesk', the '-parl' for discussion list (for parlare (it)/parler (fr) = to speak/discuss) and '-news' for low-volume announcements. You can for example subscribe [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/europarl-parl europarl-parl]. 
To repeat:
 
 * -parl is the public discussion list, you can post after you have subscribed or the moderator approves, subscription is open
 * -help is the helpdesk list, you can post easily, subscription is closed (invitation-only)
 * -news is the news list, low-volume announcement, you can subscribe, but posting is restricted 

Let us reiterate, that we would prefer that you register via http://aktiv.ffii.org/ rather than directly through mailman. In the following for the discussion lists we will point to the *-parl lists, because they are more relevant for you, but keep in mind that you also can post to the *-help lists. Eg if you got feedback from your MEP and you want to discuss it publicly, post to europarl-parl, if you got feedback from your MEP and you want to discuss it privately post to europal-help.

=== Project lists ===

A database-generated listing of projects can be found [http://www.ffii.org/proj/list/index.en.html here]. And of course there is also the [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/proj-parl/ proj-parl list] for meta-discussions of this hierarchy.

==== Lists about educating institutions (politics) ====

 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/eu0307-parl Take eg legal/media action against 07 March 2005 council "Common Position"] 
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/consilium-parl EU Council of Ministers]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/cec-parl EU Commission]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/europarl-parl European Parliament]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/bxl all kinds of events (eg a demonstration) in Brussels]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/wipo WIPO activities]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/lugs-parl EuroLUGs project]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/eniso ENISA activities]
 * For work on your government, please consult a [http://www.ffii.org/~arebenti/ekarte regional list]. Regional work is considered extremely important.

==== Lists about recurrent events (actions) ====

 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/wsis-parl WSIS]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/linuxtag-parl Linuxtag]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/messe-parl General fairs]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/prmat-parl General preparation of general PR materials]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/webdemo-parl Web demos (banners)]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/cpedu-parl General letter, calls and signature actions]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/penmi-parl General events]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/manif-parl General demonstrations]

==== Lists concerning media and supporter communictions ====

 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/media-parl work on media]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/mediaecho-parl report media echo]
The lists releg-de and releg-en (open posting, closed subscription) are used for preparation of supporter communications.

==== Lists concerning research  ====

 * Software patent granting practice: [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/patdb-parl patent PDF collection and its OCR], [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/gauss-parl/ Bayesian statistics on patents]
 * Structure of the computing industry (!SMEs vs multinationals) [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/sektor-parl (international list)], [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/sektor-de-parl (special focus on data from Germany)]
 * General legal affairs [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/jur-parl (EU English-language list)], [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/jur-fr-parl (francophone)], [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/jur-de-parl (deutschsprachig)]
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/amend-parl Discussion of good legal wordings for restricting patentability],
 * [http://lists.ffii.org/mailman/listinfo/theory-parl Advanced theory discussions on software patents] (for basic learning process please use the 'theoretic discussion' lists mentioned in the beginning).

==== FFII service email addresses ====

 * The office can be reached via buero at ffii.org (open posting, closed subscription).
 * The board can be reached via board at ffii.org (open posting, closed subscription).

